types.name: Application
types.description:
An Application, or a grouping of Entities for a single business purpose. Compared with Data Products, Applications represent a grouping of tables that exist to serve a specific
purpose. However, unlike Data Products, they don't represent groups that are tailored to be consumed for any particular purpose. Often, the assets in Applications power specific
outcomes, for example a Pricing Application.

types.name: DataContract
types.description:
A Data Contract Entity. A Data Contract is a verifiable group of assertions regarding various aspects of the data: its freshness (sla),
schema, and data quality or validity. This group of assertions represents a data owner's commitment to producing data that confirms to the agreed
upon contract. Each dataset can have a single contract. The contract can be in a "passing" or "violating" state, depending
on whether the assertions that compose the contract are passing or failing.
Note that the data contract entity is currently in early preview (beta).

fields.name: urn
fields.description: A primary key of the data contract

fields.name: type
fields.description: The standard entity type

fields.name: properties
fields.description: Properties describing the data contract

fields.name: status
fields.description: The status of the data contract

fields.name: structuredProperties
fields.description: Structured properties about this Data Contract

fields.name: relationships
fields.description: List of relationships between the source Entity and some destination entities with a given types

fields.name: entityUrn
fields.description: The urn of the related entity, e.g. the Dataset today. In the future, we may support additional contract entities.

fields.name: freshness
fields.description:
The Freshness (SLA) portion of the contract.
As of today, it is expected that there will not be more than 1 Freshness contract. If there are, only the first will be displayed.

fields.name: schema
fields.description:
The schema / structural portion of the contract.
As of today, it is expected that there will not be more than 1 Schema contract. If there are, only the first will be displayed.

fields.name: dataQuality
fields.description: A set of data quality related contracts, e.g. table and column-level contract constraints.

types.name: DataContractState
types.description: The state of the data contract

enumValues.name: ACTIVE
enumValues.description: The data contract is active.

enumValues.name: PENDING
enumValues.description: The data contract is pending. Note that this symbol is currently experimental.

fields.name: state
fields.description: The state of the data contract

i) Hiding the source in the lineage graph, if it has no downstreams

iii) Representing source sibling as a merged node, with both icons on graph and combined version in sidebar

enumValues.name: CONTAIN

enumValues.name: EQUAL
enumValues.description: Represent the relation: field = value, e.g. platform = hdfs

enumValues.name: IEQUAL
enumValues.description: Represent the relation: field = value (case-insensitive), e.g. platform = HDFS

enumValues.name: IN
enumValues.description: * Represent the relation: String field is one of the array values to, e.g. name in ["Profile", "Event"]

enumValues.description: Represents the relation: The field exists. If the field is an array, the field is either not present or empty.

enumValues.name: GREATER_THAN_OR_EQUAL_TO

enumValues.name: LESS_THAN
enumValues.description: Represent the relation less than, e.g. ownerCount < 3

enumValues.name: LESS_THAN_OR_EQUAL_TO
enumValues.description: Represent the relation less than or equal to, e.g. ownerCount <= 3

enumValues.name: START_WITH
enumValues.description: Represent the relation: String field starts with value, e.g. name starts with PageView

enumValues.name: END_WITH
enumValues.description: Represent the relation: String field ends with value, e.g. name ends with Event

enumValues.name: DESCENDANTS_INCL
enumValues.description: Represent the relation: URN field any nested children in addition to the given URN

enumValues.name: ANCESTORS_INCL
enumValues.description: Represent the relation: URN field matches any nested parent in addition to the given URN

enumValues.name: RELATED_INCL
enumValues.description: Represent the relation: URN field matches any nested child or parent in addition to the given URN

types.description:
The definition of the transformer function that should be applied to a given field / column value in a dataset
in order to determine the segment or bucket that it belongs to, which in turn is used to evaluate
volume assertions.

fields.description: The 'standard' operator type. Note that not all source systems will support all operators.

fields.name: nativeType
fields.description:
The 'native' transformer type, useful as a back door if a custom transformer is required.
This field is required if the type is NATIVE.

types.name: IncrementingSegmentFieldTransformerType
types.description: The 'standard' transformer type. Note that not all source systems will support all operators.

enumValues.name: TIMESTAMP_MS_TO_MINUTE
enumValues.description: Rounds a timestamp (in seconds) down to the start of the month.

enumValues.name: TIMESTAMP_MS_TO_HOUR
enumValues.description: Rounds a timestamp (in milliseconds) down to the nearest hour.

enumValues.name: TIMESTAMP_MS_TO_DATE
enumValues.description: Rounds a timestamp (in milliseconds) down to the start of the day.

enumValues.name: TIMESTAMP_MS_TO_MONTH
enumValues.description: Rounds a timestamp (in milliseconds) down to the start of the month

enumValues.name: TIMESTAMP_MS_TO_YEAR
enumValues.description: Rounds a timestamp (in milliseconds) down to the start of the year

enumValues.name: FLOOR
enumValues.description: Rounds a numeric value down to the nearest integer.

enumValues.name: CEILING
enumValues.description: Rounds a numeric value up to the nearest integer.

enumValues.name: NATIVE
enumValues.description:
A backdoor to provide a native operator type specific to a given source system like
Snowflake, Redshift, BQ, etc.

types.name: IncrementingSegmentSpec
types.description:
Core attributes required to identify an incrementing segment in a table. This type is mainly useful
for tables that constantly increase with new rows being added on a particular cadence (e.g. fact or event tables).

An incrementing segment represents a logical chunk of data which is INSERTED
into a dataset on a regular interval, along with the presence of a constantly-incrementing column
value such as an event time, date partition, or last modified column.

An incrementing segment is principally identified by 2 key attributes combined:

1. A field or column that represents the incrementing value. New rows that are inserted will be identified using this column.
   Note that the value of this column may not by itself represent the "bucket" or the "segment" in which the row falls.

2. [Optional] An transformer function that may be applied to the selected column value in order
   to obtain the final "segment identifier" or "bucket identifier". Rows that have the same value after applying the transformation
   will be grouped into the same segment, using which the final value (e.g. row count) will be determined.

fields.name: field
fields.description: The field to use to generate segments. It must be constantly incrementing as new rows are inserted.

fields.name: transformer
fields.description:
Optional transformer function to apply to the field in order to obtain the final segment or bucket identifier.
If not provided, then no operator will be applied to the field. (identity function)

types.name: UpsertDataContractInput
types.description: Input required to upsert a Data Contract entity for an asset

inputFields.name: entityUrn
inputFields.description: The urn of the related entity. Dataset is the only entity type supported today.

inputFields.name: freshness
inputFields.description:
The Freshness / Freshness portion of the contract. If not provided, this will be set to none.
For Dataset Contracts, it is expected that there will not be more than 1 Freshness contract. If there are, only the first will be displayed.

inputFields.name: schema
inputFields.description:
The schema / structural portion of the contract. If not provided, this will be set to none.
For Dataset Contracts, it is expected that there will not be more than 1 Schema contract. If there are, only the first will be displayed.

inputFields.name: dataQuality
inputFields.description: The data quality portion of the contract. If not provided, this will be set to none.

inputFields.name: state
inputFields.description: The state of the data contract. If not provided, it will be in ACTIVE mode by default.

inputFields.name: id
inputFields.description:
Optional ID of the contract you want to create. Only applicable if this is a create operation. If not provided, a random
id will be generated for you.

types.name: VolumeAssertionInfo
types.description: A definition of a Volume (row count) assertion.

fields.name: entityUrn
fields.description: The entity targeted by this Volume check.

fields.name: type
fields.description: The type of the freshness assertion being monitored.

fields.name: rowCountTotal
fields.description:
Produce FAILURE Assertion Result if the row count of the asset does not meet specific requirements.
Required if type is 'ROW_COUNT_TOTAL'.

fields.name: rowCountChange
fields.description:
Produce FAILURE Assertion Result if the row count delta of the asset does not meet specific requirements.
Required if type is 'ROW_COUNT_CHANGE'.

fields.name: incrementingSegmentRowCountTotal
fields.description:
Produce FAILURE Assertion Result if the latest incrementing segment row count total of the asset
does not meet specific requirements. Required if type is 'INCREMENTING_SEGMENT_ROW_COUNT_TOTAL'.

fields.name: incrementingSegmentRowCountChange
fields.description:
Produce FAILURE Assertion Result if the incrementing segment row count delta of the asset
does not meet specific requirements. Required if type is 'INCREMENTING_SEGMENT_ROW_COUNT_CHANGE'.

fields.name: filter
fields.description:
A definition of the specific filters that should be applied, when performing monitoring.
If not provided, there is no filter, and the full table is under consideration.

types.name: VolumeAssertionType
types.description: A type of volume (row count) assertion

enumValues.name: ROW_COUNT_TOTAL
enumValues.description: A volume assertion that is evaluated against the total row count of a dataset.

enumValues.name: ROW_COUNT_CHANGE
enumValues.description:
A volume assertion that is evaluated against an incremental row count of a dataset,
or a row count change.

enumValues.name: INCREMENTING_SEGMENT_ROW_COUNT_TOTAL
enumValues.description:
A volume assertion that checks the latest "segment" in a table based on an incrementing
column to check whether it's row count falls into a particular range.
This can be used to monitor the row count of an incrementing date-partition column segment.

enumValues.name: INCREMENTING_SEGMENT_ROW_COUNT_CHANGE
enumValues.description:
A volume assertion that compares the row counts in neighboring "segments" or "partitions"
of an incrementing column. This can be used to track changes between subsequent date partition
in a table, for example.
